# plugin_echo Build Instructions

## Prerequisites

- CMake 3.10+
- C++17 compiler
  - Windows: MSVC or MinGW-w64 (posix thread model)
  - Linux: GCC or Clang

## Build Commands

### Windows + MSVC
```bash
cmake --preset msvc
cmake --build build --config Release
```

### Windows + MinGW (posix)
```bash
cmake --preset mingw-posix
cmake --build build
```

### Linux
```bash
mkdir build && cd build
cmake ..
make
```

## Output

- Windows: `build/bin/plugin_echo.dll`
- Linux: `build/lib/libplugin_echo.so`

## SDK Structure

```
sdk/
├── include/           # Header files
│   ├── luo9_sdk.h
│   ├── bot.h
│   ├── bus.h
│   ├── command.h
│   ├── message.h
│   ├── payload.h
│   ├── pattern.h
│   └── version.h
└── lib/
    ├── windows/
    │   ├── luo9_sdk_cpp.lib        # SDK static lib (MSVC)
    │   ├── libluo9_sdk_cpp_mingw.a # SDK static lib (MinGW)
    │   ├── luo9_core.lib           # Core import lib
    │   └── luo9_core.dll           # Core runtime
    └── linux/
        ├── libluo9_sdk_cpp.a       # SDK static lib
        └── libluo9_core.so         # Core shared lib
```

## Usage Example

```cpp
#include "luo9_sdk.h"

using namespace luo9::command;
using namespace luo9::bot;

void handle_msg(uint64_t group_id, const std::string& msg) {
    auto cmd = Command::parse(msg, "echo", PrefixMode::Optional('/'));
    if (!cmd.empty()) {
        send_group_msg(group_id, cmd.args_raw());
    }
}
```
